"Verdict: A delicious Gose from De Garde. Really puckery and tart but with nice complexity for a simple and refreshing style. This beer looks like hell, but really hits the spot, salty, floral, tart and super drinkable, I'd love to knock this beer back all day in the summer months."
""
""
""
"Bottle poured into a Prairie 2nd Anniversary stem glass (while I'm waiting for my dG stem glass to arrive). Complete silence on opening the cap, indicating low or no carbonation. An aggressive pour yielded a completely lifeless liquid, no carbonation whatsoever, no head; murky orange-yellow color. In the aroma, lots of raw citrus oils, and not much else. Similarly in the taste, loads of citrus zest and oil, mostly grapefruit, with strong additions of orange and lemon, light coriander spice, and an unmistakable salty finish. The mouthfeel really suffered by the complete lack of carbonation, turning what would have probably been a very good gose into a glass of citrus juice. Even a slight bubbly tingle would have been a major improvement, but it just wasn't here. Overall tasty, but kind of hard to drink,due solely to the carbonation (lack thereof)."
