"Bottle from Sam by way of Brian. Thanks! Pouring a mostly clear light orange yellow with a dense, off-white head that falls off to a ring leaving little lacing, this looks solid. The nose is just incredible. Bright, juicy, fruity hops with a moderate amount of coriander, beautifully paired to amplify each others strengths along with a little bit of citron and lemon, this just smells incredible. In some ways, this is not unlike jal-jeera,. Coriander character is bright and fresh, lightly toasted. Salt is minimal. Some mild gin-like aromatics are also present. The palate opens quite sour with a big citrusy sourness, lemony and moderately potent along with a mild coriander note. The citrus sourness pairs beautifully with the hops, juicy and fruity with a blend of citrus, tropical fruit (pineapple, mango, guava). Mildly briny on the finish along with some citrus sourness, this is incredible stuff. Highly recommended."
